#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:1
msgid "Changing buttons on page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:4
msgid "Support for \"edit this page\" link."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:8
msgid "Support for \"view this page\" link."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:11
msgid ""
"Furo can add buttons to each document that links visitors to the document's "
"sources on the repository's source control system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:13
msgid ""
"This feature is inherited from [sphinx-basic-ng](https://sphinx-basic-ng."
"readthedocs.io/en/latest/), specifically the [`view-this-page.html`](https://"
"sphinx-basic-ng.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage/components/view-this-page/) "
"and [`edit-this-page`](https://sphinx-basic-ng.readthedocs.io/en/latest/"
"usage/components/edit-this-page/) components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:15
msgid "With popular VCS hosts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:17
msgid ""
"Provide the relevant VCS variables, by setting the following keys in "
"[`html_theme_options`][sphinx-html_theme_options]:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:19
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"source_repository\": \"https://github.com/pradyunsg/furo/\",\n"
"    \"source_branch\": \"main\",\n"
"    \"source_directory\": \"docs/\",\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:27
msgid ""
"This model supports github.com, gitlab.com and bitbucket.org as domain names "
"for the `source_repository` key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:29
msgid "With arbitrary URLs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:32
msgid "`source_edit_link`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:36
msgid "`source_view_link`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:39
msgid ""
"Use arbitrary URLs for the view/edit buttons, by setting the following keys "
"in [`html_theme_options`][sphinx-html_theme_options]:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:41
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"source_edit_link\": \"https://my.awesome.host.example.com/awesome/"
"project/edit/{filename}\",\n"
"    \"source_view_link\": \"https://my.awesome.host.example.com/awesome/"
"project/view/{filename}\",\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:48
msgid ""
"The `{filename}` component will be replaced with the full path to the file, "
"as known from the base of the documentation directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:51
msgid ""
"Furo does not enforce that the `source_edit_link` / `source_view_link` "
"contain `{filename}` or any sort of correctness check on these URLs. Make "
"sure to manually confirm that the link works."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:54
msgid "Linking to copied sources"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:56
msgid ""
"If [`html_show_sourcelink`](https://www.sphinx-doc.org/en/master/usage/"
"configuration.html#confval-html_show_sourcelink) and [`html_copy_source`]"
"(https://www.sphinx-doc.org/en/master/usage/configuration.html#confval-"
"html_copy_source) are `True` (which are the defaults), and the documentation "
"does not configure any of the above variables, the view button will link to "
"the raw sources copied in by Sphinx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:58
msgid "Read the Docs support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:65
msgid "This feature is only available for projects hosted on GitHub."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:68
msgid ""
"Furo has built-in support for inferring details from Read the Docs' "
"environment for GitHub projects and enabling these buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:70
msgid ""
"For such projects, Furo will try to automatically infer the source "
"repository, branch, and directory from the Read the Docs build environment "
"unless the above configuration variable are set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:72
msgid "Edit button on Read the Docs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:74
msgid "The _edit_ button will link to GitHub's edit view for the document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:76
msgid "View button on Read the Docs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:78
msgid ""
"The _view_ button will link to the raw sources copied in by Sphinx, if "
"available, [as noted above](#linking-to-copied-sources). If raw sources are "
"not copied, it will link to GitHub's plain view for the document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:80
msgid ""
"If you do not want to link to copied sources, you can set the following in "
"the `conf.py`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:82
msgid ""
"html_copy_source = False\n"
"html_show_sourcelink = False\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:87
msgid "Disabling on Read the Docs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:94
msgid "`top_of_page_buttons` replaces the singular `top_of_page_button`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/top-of-page-buttons.md:97
msgid ""
"If you wish to disable these default buttons, use {ref}`top_of_page_buttons` "
"and set it to `[]`."
msgstr ""
